You can cause git to show textual diffs between versions of
OpenDocument files by doing the following.

$ git config --global diff.odf.textconv odt2txt
$ git config --global core.attributesfile ~/.gitattributes-odf
$ cat >> ~/.gitattributes-odf <<EOF
*.ods diff=odf
*.odt diff=odf
*.odp diff=odf
EOF

Alternatively, diff.odf.textconv can be set for the current
repository, and the attributes can be set by putting the attribute
text into either a .gitattributes file in some directory inside the
repository along the path to the files in question, or in the
.git/info/attributes file.

Reference: http://www-verimag.imag.fr/~moy/opendocument/

 -- Barak A. Pearlmutter <bap@debian.org>, Wed,  2 Nov 2011 11:24:59 +0000
